<item>Construct a table or a tree diagram of the situation. Include a branch for all other modes of transportation to work.</item>
<item>Assuming that the walkers walk alone, what percent of all commuters travel alone to work?</item>
<item>Suppose that 1,000 workers are randomly selected. How many would you expect to travel alone to work?</item>
<item>Suppose that 1,000 workers are randomly selected. How many would you expect to drive in a carpool?</item></list></problem>
